                                         JOHANNESBURG - The N3 at Van Reenen’s Pass between Harrismith and Ladysmith has been fully reopened to traffic following two major accidents earlier on Friday. Two people died in a multi-vehicle crash involving three trucks and three minibuses, while a third person died in a separate collision involving two trucks.  The N3 Toll Concession’s Con Roux said: “The N3 has been fully reopened at Van Reenen’s Pass. This after the road had been closed following two serious crashes as well as a separate 4km diesel spill. Massive word of appreciation to all the clean-up crew and the emergency personnel who attended these crashes.”  (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)